We begin our investigation with the contrast between the solo and group conditions. To measure group creativity, we take the average cosine similarity to the target noun over all guesses by all participants over all 25 rounds of each game. This value, which is typically small but positive, is the dependent variable in all analyses (unless otherwise noted). Our results from a regression model using the no-bot condition as the reference variable show that working as a group adds a significant benefit over members acting in isolation (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
